President Jacob Zuma will take the Public Protector s state capture report on review. The presidency issued a statement on Friday stating that the President has considered and also sought legal advice on the contents of the report as well as the remedial action to be taken. The legal advice given, and which advice has been accepted by the President, is to take the remedial action on review. The statement added that the president s legal team has been briefed and is working on the review application, and that the basis for the review will be set out in the review application.Former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela s report on state capture ordered Zuma to appoint a judicial enquiry to investigate various allegations of state capture. The enquiry would be chaired by a judge nominated by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng.Earlier this week Zuma said in the National Assembly that the report wasn t fair to him and many other individuals.He said only the president has the right to appoint a judicial enquiry and that no-one can instruct the president to appoint such a commission.